    "Thus, 2B L ∞ ∩ Em(P d), may be covered by a countable union of weak * nowhere dense sets, which by definition makes it a first category set in the sense of Baire.",
    "Since 2B L ∞ equipped with the weak * topology is a completely metrisable space, the Baire category theorem may be applied in this case to assert that 2B L ∞ \\ Em(P d) is weak * dense inside 2B L ∞.",
    "This is in the spirit of the results of Dymond et al [22].",
    "Since the Baire categorical considerations are a matter of applying a standard theorem, we state the intermediate result in a convenient form.",
    "Since ρ n is smooth, it holds that ρ ∈ Em(P d), by taking for example f 1 = ρ, π 1 = Id and f i = 0, π i = 0 for i ≥ 2."
